&lt;p&gt;Band 6 Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Permanent 37.5 hours&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Come and join our friendly, sociable, experienced teams working within the Integrated Discharge Team (IDT) at Conquest Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The IDT facilitates the rapid assessment of patients within the hospital environment in order to support the timely and safe discharge of patients from the acute setting. This may require follow-up in patients homes or other community environment, taking a &#39;home first&#39; approach to hospital discharges. As an OT working within the IDT you will be offered a broad range of experience working with patients, and will be part of an experienced team which is key to managing patient flow within our acute sites. You will have the opportunity to work towards cross-professional competencies which aims to broaden our therapists scope of practice and support with enhanced assessment skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our IDT Teams offer friendly, supportive, multi professional working. You will be fully supported to develop your specific OT and inter-professional skills, and areas of special clinical interest relevant to the role. We offer regular supervision and training opportunities for professional development.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We encourage you to contact us for an informal chat or visit. We look forward to hearing from you&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emma Chapman, Team Lead OT - Integrated Discharge Service, emma.chapman3@nhs.net 01424 755255 extn 148144&lt;/p&gt;
